  "title": "Snake AND Spider Found in the Same Australian Bedroom",
  "script": "Snake AND spider — same bedroom? Stuart McKenzie from Sunshine Coast Snake Catchers in Queensland, Australia got called to remove a python. Standard job. He walked in, spotted the carpet python on the floor — then looked up. Above the headboard: a huntsman spider the absolute size of a dinner plate. McKenzie said it was one of the biggest he'd ever seen in his years doing this. He used a snake hook to wrangle the python, then — this is real — pulled off his own hat to catch the spider. Both got released outside, unharmed. The homeowners got their bedroom back. Probably still lying awake staring at the ceiling. Are Australians even surprised at this point?",
